  "texts": [
    "Moreover, expert oversight of the final LLM output could mitigate any remaining risks in the last instance, ensuring that erroneous or inappropriate suggestions are identified and corrected before they can impact patient care.",
    "Recently, efforts have been made in this direction by adopting the widely recognized Physician Documentation Quality Instrument (PDQI-9) for the assessment of AI transcripts and clinical summaries 147.",
    "However, whether ongoing human oversight and validation of LLM-generated content is feasible and can reduce the likelihood of adverse outcomes remains the subject of further research at this early stage of LLM deployment in healthcare.",
    "Another important factor for the successful clinical implementation of LLMs in patient care could be patient acceptance, which was not assessed in any of the studies analyzed.",
    "The growing use of LLMs in healthcare might be perceived as a reduction in the interpersonal relationship between healthcare professionals and patients, potentially leading to a sense of dehumanization in medicine 148."
